      • getElementIdAt

        public String getElementIdAt(int index)
        Returns null.

        Get an unique ID for the element. This ID will be used in some mediums to find the element in the case where the model and user interface become inconsistent. When accessing the model, the ID may be used to find the element index.

        This method may return null if not supported.

        Specified by:
        getElementIdAt in interface ListModel
        Parameters:
        index - The index, in the interval [0,getSize()).
        Returns:
